result.execSummary:
The defendant Joseph J. Trentadue was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/ Intent-THC (>10,000 g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)5.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: If revoked, deft requests credit for approximately three months of jail time.

miscConds.notes: Bond applied  -  Balance still due.    If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.  
*  Pay supervision fees.  
*  Pay fine of $7000  and court costs including all applicable surcharges.  
*  Bond to apply  (Balance due in 2 years or deft shall be returned to court).   
*  Submit to a DNA (unless previously provided) sample and pay surcharge.  
The Dept shall promptly notify the Court of any new arrest or criminal charge made against the deft.
